# ==============================================================================
# LIFELOG ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION TEMPLATE
# ==============================================================================
# Instructions for Local Development (Windows):
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to `.env.local` in your project root folder.
# 2. Replace the placeholder values below with your actual Supabase credentials.
# 3. DO NOT wrap the values in double quotes ("") or single quotes ('').
# 4. DO NOT include any trailing spaces or slashes at the end of the lines.
#
# Instructions for Vercel Production Deployment (`prod`):
# 1. Go to your Vercel Dashboard -> Select LifeLog Project -> Settings -> Environment Variables.
# 2. Add BOTH of the variables below exactly as shown (Key and Value).
# 3. Check all environments (Production, Preview, Development).
# 4. Once saved, click "Deployments" tab -> three dots (...) on top commit -> "Redeploy".
# ==============================================================================

# 1. Your Supabase Project URL
# Find this in: Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API -> Project URL
# Format: https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# 2. Your Supabase Anonymous API Key (Public/Anon Key)
# Find this in: Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API -> Project API keys -> `anon` (`public`)
# Format: A long JWT string starting with `eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsIn...`
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.placeholder
